SIMPLE: superciliary
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Superciliary
<hw>Su`per*cil"i*a*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>supercilium</ets> an eyebrow. See <er>Supercilious</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the eyebrows;
supraorbital.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having a distinct streak of color
above the eyes; <as>as, the <ex>superciliary</ex>
woodpecker</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supercilious</ent>⟦br⟧
